  "prompt": "What is a good inpatient drug and alcohol rehab center in Wayne County IA?",
  "response": "Wayne County, IA, is a rural area with limited options for inpatient drug and alcohol rehab centers. However, there are nearby facilities and resources in surrounding regions that may be suitable. Here are some options to consider:\n\n### **Nearby Inpatient Rehab Centers:**\n1. **Clarinda Regional Health Center**  \n   - Address: 220 Essie Davison Dr, Clarinda, IA 51632  \n   - Services: Offers behavioral health and substance abuse treatment programs, including inpatient care.  \n   - Distance: Approximately 1.5 hours from Wayne County.  \n\n2. **Oak Place \u2013 Centerville**  \n   - Address: 1 Parkway Dr, Centerville, IA 52544  \n   - Services: Provides residential substance abuse treatment for adults.  \n   - Distance: Approximately 1 hour from Wayne County.  \n\n3. **Crossroads Behavioral Health Services**  \n   - Address: 1409 W Townline Rd, Creston, IA 50801  \n   - Services: Offers inpatient and outpatient substance abuse treatment.  \n   - Distance: Approximately 1.5 hours from Wayne County.  \n\n### **Additional Resources:**\n- **Iowa Department of Public Health \u2013 Substance Abuse Services**:  \n  They can help you locate licensed treatment facilities in Iowa. Visit [their website](https://idph.iowa.gov/substance-abuse) or call (515) 281-3641.  \n- **SAMHSA National Helpline**:  \n  Call 1-800-662-HELP (4357) for free, confidential assistance in finding treatment options nationwide.  \n\nIt\u2019s also worth checking with local healthcare providers or community organizations in Wayne County for recommendations or referrals. If transportation is an issue, some facilities may offer telehealth services or assistance with travel arrangements.",
